        section#esact
            .container
                .text-center.mt-4
                    h1 About EsACT

                .decptext.text-start.mb-5.pb-5
                    p.lead The School of Communication, Administration and Tourism of Mirandela is a decentralized organic unit of the Polytechnic Institute of Bragança, located in the city of Mirandela, right in the geographical center of the region of Trás-os-Montes and Alto Douro.
                    p.lead The School initially emerged as a branch of the School of Technology and Management of Bragança. Three years later, it adopted an autonomous structure, taking the name of Escola Superior de Tecnologia e Gestão de Mirandela. Since then, it has been felt that, despite the distance that separates them, the School should evolve independently, with an identity and skills that would distinguish it within the IPB. With the restructuring of the IPB Statutes, approved in December 2008, the School adopted the designation of School of Communication, Administration and Tourism of Mirandela, formalizing the desired differentiation, already evident in the training offer.

            .mainimg(style="background-image: url('../../../imgs/esact.jpg');")
            .container
                .decptext.text-start
                    p.lead The emerging areas of Communication and Tourism, considered as critical and crucial valences both for the School and for the development of the municipality in relation to the current society and the guidelines issued by the community guidelines, are assumed as strategic, taking advantage of the existing technological resources, the concentration of services, the dynamism of the offices and companies that take advantage of the resources that the school trains, along with the region's heritage and cultural resources.


